cAP. VI.

Argument. My client’ s father, Sextius Roscius, was a burgess of Ameria wealthy and of good birth, and a staunch supporter of the aristocratic party, whose cause he espoused in the late civil trouble (between Marius and Sulla), and with some of the leaders of which he was on terms of the closest ln- timacy. Unfortunately, there was a long· -standing and bitter feud between him and his two kinsmen, bRoscius Capito and Roscius Magnus, men of the lowest character.
